Business Description

Project Name: Operational Process Efficiency Tracker (OPET)

Description:
OPET is a web-based application designed to help organizations monitor and improve operational processes. It provides real-time tracking of processing times, identifies bottlenecks, and monitors resource utilization, enabling business analysts and operations managers to make data-driven decisions and optimize workflows.

Use Case:

Track task processing times across departments.

Identify operational bottlenecks causing delays.

Analyze staff or resource utilization for efficiency improvements.

Generate reports and dashboards for management review.

Business Case:
Companies spend significant time and resources on inefficient processes. By using OPET, organizations can:

Reduce process delays and costs.

Allocate resources more effectively.

Increase productivity and throughput.

Make informed decisions using actionable analytics.

2️⃣ Features

User authentication: Secure login for admins and team leads.

Task tracking: Add tasks, assign resources, track start/end times.

Bottleneck analysis: Visualize tasks with delays and high processing times.

Resource utilization: Track resource workload and idle times.

Dashboard: Charts showing average processing time, bottlenecks, and resource efficiency.

Exportable reports: CSV/Excel download of tracked data.

3️⃣ Tech Stack

Backend: Python + Flask

Database: SQLite (can be replaced by MySQL/PostgreSQL for production)

Frontend: HTML + Bootstrap + Chart.js

Hosting/Deployment: Any cloud provider supporting Python/Flask (Heroku, Render, PythonAnywhere)

Version Control: GitHub
